# Code Conventions for MedFund

## TypeScript Conventions

- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Define interfaces for all data structures
- Use type inference where appropriate
- Prefer readonly properties for immutable data

## React Conventions

- Use functional components with hooks
- Organize components in a logical folder structure
- Use React Router for navigation
- Apply shadcn/ui components for UI consistency

## Database/ORM Conventions

- Use Drizzle ORM for database operations
- Define schemas in dedicated schema files
- Use relations correctly for related data
- Implement proper error handling for database operations

## File Structure

- `/src/lib/db` - Database related files (schema, migrations, client)
- `/src/components` - React components
- `/src/pages` - Main application pages
- `/src/hooks` - Custom React hooks
- `/src/integrations` - Third-party integrations
